* Editor's note: Please be aware the video attached above contains graphic descriptions of violence. JOHANNESBURG - The police officer who allegedly shot and killed his wife is expected back in court on 13 July for a formal bail application. Cato Ridge community members protested outside the court in support of the family on Monday. READ: KZN police officer in court for allegedly killing wife Nontuthuko Msomi, a family member, described the family's reaction: "Obviously we're happy, this is only the beginning but for now, we're happy. "We'll have to wait to see what will happen on the 13th [of July] but for now we're happy."